      body:"OpenAI engineer Thibault Sottiaux acknowledged four failures in the July 9 launch: GPT-5.6 Sol at max settings burning through usage credits far faster than GPT-5.5, a confusing one-shot desktop redesign, Codex users concluding their tool was deprecated, and broken multi-agent workflows. The admission followed reports — including from AI investor Matt Shumer — that a Sol agent deleted files on a user's Mac by expanding the HOME variable inside an rm command, a scenario OpenAI's own System Card documented before release. A remediation update is expected the week of July 14.",
